main event: The document describes a sighting of a small, light-colored oval object moving in a straight, level course at a constant speed with a slight increase in brightness momentarily. The object was observed by a ground observer and could not be definitively identified.
interesting points: The object appeared larger than a star and moved rapidly on a straight course across the sky for approximately 30 degrees, giving off a greenish-colored light.
The sighting was observed by two independent witnesses on board a ship, who stated it was something they had never seen before and could not identify.
The document indicates the object could possibly be a meteor, but could not be definitely identified.
The document is a Project 10073 record card, suggesting it is from the Project Blue Book archive of UFO reports.
The document also includes a separate analysis sheet that discusses the sighting, including the location, date, time, and evaluation of the source's reliability as 'poor - possible reliable'.
witnesses: ground observer, two independent witnesses on board ship
